   <note>This is a photograph of a poster from the Sumner County Colored Agricultural Fair, which took place August 25-27,1938. The poster noted that the officers were Simon Patterson, president, and Hardy Hall, Vice-president. The event billed itself as "American's First Negro Fair" and encouraged people to "Keep Your Children in Union High School."</note>
